#: ../../mail.rst:32
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:34
msgid ""
"The mail module requires at least one :ref:`user domain <user-domains-"
"section>` already configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:36
msgid "The first configuration wizard will require the following information:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:38
msgid ""
"``Mail server hostname``: insert the mail server name, this should be the"
" same name configured inside your MX DNS record"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:40
msgid ""
"``Primary mail domain``: insert the mail domain, like ``nethserver.org``;"
" you will be able to add more domains later"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:43
msgid ""
"Then, select the user domain to be connected to the mail server. An email"
" address will be created for every user in the selected domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:50
msgid "Domains"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:52
msgid ""
"NethServer can handle an unlimited number of mail domains, configurable "
"from the ``Domains`` page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:55
msgid ""
"If a domain is deleted, email will not be deleted; any message already "
"received is preserved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:58
msgid ""
"You can add a new domain by clicking on the :guilabel:`Create domain` "
"button and fill the ``Name`` field with the mail domain, like "
"``mymail.org``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:61
msgid ""
"If the fist option is disabled, you can enable the ``Accept unknown "
"recipients`` switch and select a mailbox that will catch all messages "
"sent to non-existing addresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:64
msgid ""
"NethServer allows storing an hidden copy of all messages directed to a "
"particular domain: they will be delivered to the final recipient *and "
"also* to a custom email address. The hidden copy is enabled by the "
":guilabel:`Copy inbound messages` switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:69
msgid ""
"On some countries, enabling the *Copy inbound messages* switch can be "
"against privacy laws."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:72
msgid ""
"If the final recipient cannot be established (i.e. the recipient address "
"does not exist), the message is normally rejected. Sometimes (i.e. when a"
" mail domain is migrated) it could be useful to accept it and silently "
"deliver the message to a catch-all mailbox. This behavior can be obtained"
" by enabling the ``Accept unknown recipients`` option. This configuration"
" is available only if ``Add user address from user domain`` option is "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:80
msgid "DKIM signature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:82
msgid "DKIM is not currently configurable from the web user interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:84
msgid ""
"DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) provides a way to validate the sending "
"MTA, which adds a cryptographic signature to the outbound message MIME "
"headers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:88
msgid ""
"The DKIM signature headers are added only to messages sent through TCP "
"ports 587 (submission) and 465 (smtps)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:91
msgid ""
"To work effectively, the public DNS must be configured properly. Refer to"
" the instructions of your DNS provider to run the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:94
msgid ""
"Add a TXT record to your public DNS service provider with key "
"\"default._domainKey\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:96
msgid "Copy and paste the given key text in the DNS record data (RDATA) section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:102
msgid "Mailboxes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:104
msgid ""
"Each user has a personal mailbox and any user name in the form "
"*<username>@<domain>* is also a valid email address to deliver messages "
"into it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:107
msgid ""
"The list of mailboxes is shown by the ``Mailboxes`` page. There are two "
"types of mailboxes: users and public mailboxes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:111
msgid "Users mailboxes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:113
msgid ""
"You can disable each mailbox by selecting the ``Disable`` item from the "
"three-dots menu on the mailbox line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:115
msgid ""
"By clicking the ``Edit`` item from the three-dots menu it's possible to "
"setup the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:117
msgid "``Forward messages``: forward all messages to another mail address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:118
msgid ""
"``Custom mailbox quota``: override the quota configured from the :ref"
":`mail_settings-section`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:119
msgid ""
"``Custom spam retention``: override the retention configured from the "
":ref:`mail_settings-section`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:122
msgid "Public mailboxes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:124
msgid ""
"Public mailboxes can be shared among groups of users. The "
":guilabel:`Create public mailbox` button allows creating a new public "
"mailbox and defining one or more owning groups and users. Public "
"mailboxes can also be created by any IMAP client supporting IMAP ACL "
"protocol extension (RFC 4314)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:129
msgid ""
"When a new public mailbox is created, the mail server will automatically "
"add a new address for all existing mail domains."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:136
msgid "Addresses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:138
msgid ""
"In addition to the users, groups and public mailboxes addresses, "
"described in the previous section, the system enables the creation of an "
"unlimited number of email addresses, from the ``Addresses`` page. Each "
"mail address is associated with one or more destinations. A destination "
"can be of the following types:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:144
msgid "user mailbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:145
msgid "public mailbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:146
msgid "external email address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:148
msgid ""
"A mail address can be bound to any mail domain or be specific to one mail"
" domain. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:151
msgid "First domain: ``mydomain.net``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:152
msgid "Second domain: ``example.com``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:153
msgid ""
"Email address *info* bound to any domain: ``info@mydomain.net``, "
"``info@example.com``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:155
msgid "Email address *goofy* specific to one domain: ``goofy@example.com``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:157
msgid ""
"Sometimes a company forbids communications from outside the organization "
"using personal email addresses. The ``Internal`` check box blocks the "
"possibility of an address to receive messages from the outside. Still an "
"*internal* address can be used to exchange messages with other accounts "
"of the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:166
msgid "Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:168
msgid "All transiting email messages are subjected to a list of checks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:170 ../../mail.rst:176
msgid "Antivirus"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:171 ../../mail.rst:185
msgid "Antispam"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:178
msgid ""
"The antivirus component finds email messages containing viruses. Infected"
" messages are discarded. The virus signature database is updated "
"periodically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:187
msgid ""
"The antispam component RSPAMD analyzes emails by detecting and "
"classifying `SPAM <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spamming>`_ messages "
"using heuristic criteria, predetermined rules and statistical evaluations"
" on the content of messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:192
msgid ""
"The filter can also check if sender server is listed in one or more block"
" lists (`DNSBL <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spamming>`_). A score is "
"associated to each rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:195
msgid ""
"Total spam score collected at the end of the analysis allows the server "
"to decide what to do with a message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:198
msgid ""
"Statistical filters, called `Bayesian <https://www.blu-system.com"
"/sicurezza-informatica-pavia-blu-system>`_, are special rules that evolve"
" and quickly adapt analyzing messages marked as **spam** or **ham**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:205
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:207
msgid "From the ``Settings`` page, you can configure the ``Default mail quota``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:209
msgid ""
"If the general mailbox quota is enabled, the ``Mailboxes`` page "
"summarizes the quota usage for each user. This summary is updated when a "
"user logs in or a message is delivered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:213
msgid ""
"Messages marked as **spam** (see :ref:`email_filter`) can be "
"automatically moved into the ``Junk`` folder by enabling the option "
"``Move spam to junk folder``. Spam messages can be expunged automatically"
" after a period of time. You can configure it from the ``Default spam "
"retention`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../mail.rst:218
msgid ""
"From the ``Master users`` section, you can setup a user than can "
"impersonate another user, gaining full rights to any mailbox contents and"
" folder permissions."
msgstr ""

